## Code-side reading

- src/bearings/agent/routing.py — `evaluate()` at L148-249. Function
  takes `quota_snapshot: QuotaSnapshot | None`, calls
  `quota_snapshot.quota_state_dict()` exactly once (L201) and threads
  the resulting dict into every returned RoutingDecision via
  `quota_state_at_decision=quota_state`. The dict is *not* used in
  any decision branch — purely a dataclass-population channel.
- src/bearings/agent/quota.py — `apply_quota_guard()` at L123-216.
  Always recomputes `new_state = snapshot.quota_state_dict()` (L161)
  and either folds it onto the unchanged decision via
  `replace(decision, quota_state_at_decision=new_state)` (L206) or
  rebuilds the decision with `quota_state_at_decision=new_state` (L215).
  Every code path in the guard overwrites the field.
- src/bearings/agent/quota.py:102-115 — `quota_state_dict()` uses
  `self.overall_used_pct or 0.0` / `self.sonnet_used_pct or 0.0`
  (audit's "minor 7"). Conflates legitimate 0.0 with None — the
  type contract on the underlying field is `float | None` and the
  `or` test treats 0.0 as falsy.
- src/bearings/agent/override_aggregator.py — Pass 2 origin CTE at
  L267-289. Outer `WITH origin AS (...)` selects messages whose
  `m.id` matches the earliest message of `m.session_id` (inner
  subquery L273-277). The inner subquery has *no time predicate*:
  it selects the all-time earliest rule-bearing message per session.
  The outer override CTE (L280-284) does include the cutoff filter
  on `created_at`, so the audit's "any scenario where a manual
  message appears inside the window for an out-of-window session
  would inflate the numerator silently" is exactly the gap.
- src/bearings/db/routing.py:343-359 — `list_for_tags()` is a Python
  loop calling `list_for_tag()` once per tag id; one SELECT per tag.
  Audit's "minor 4" stands.
- src/bearings/db/routing.py:224-243 / web/routes/routing.py:142-173
  — `create_tag_rule` route catches every `aiosqlite.IntegrityError`
  as 404 "tag not found". Audit's "minor 5" stands.
- src/bearings/db/routing.py:246-260, 405-419, 562-576, 677-691 —
  phantom dataclass instances (`RoutingRule(id=0, …)` /
  `SystemRoutingRule(id=0, …)`) constructed and discarded for
  validation side-effect. Audit's "minor 6" stands.
- src/bearings/web/routes/_deps.py — exists. `_db` and
  `_quota_poller` defined here at L33-63; module docstring
  explicitly cites V1_FEATURE_AUDIT.md feature 3 finding 3 as the
  motivation. routes/routing.py:52, routes/quota.py:26,
  routes/usage.py:33 all import from `bearings.web.routes._deps`.
  No duplication remains.
- `git log --oneline --follow src/bearings/web/routes/_deps.py` →
  bda4c513 refactor(web): extract _db/_quota_poller into routes/_deps.py
  (resolves audit feature-3 minor #3).

## Caller audit for defect 1

Two production callers of evaluate():
- src/bearings/web/routes/routing.py:395-401 — preview endpoint;
  passes `snapshot` to both evaluate() and apply_quota_guard().
- src/bearings/agent/session_assembly.py:289-296 — assembly path;
  passes `snapshot` to both evaluate() and apply_quota_guard().

Both callers pass the same snapshot to both functions; the audit's
"every caller passes the same snapshot to both functions" is exact.

